## Fix DT status regression — missing lakebase fields & stale cache

Context: After the TODO.md changes, users reported the Build and Cockpit pages
showed "Not found" / "Not loaded" badges for Triple-Store and Graph DB even
after a successful DT generation. Root causes: the build session cache was
missing the new `lakebase_table_exists` field (showing "Not found" on live
checks), the cockpit `/validate/detailed` response omitted all lakebase-specific
fields, and `_loadDtExistence()` didn't call `_applyBuildGraphEngineUi` so the
Table badge was never refreshed after a build.

Changes:

1. src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py
   Added `lakebase_table_exists`, `view_table`, and `registry_archive_applicable`
   to the post-build session cache so badges show correct state immediately.
2. src/back/objects/domain/HomeService.py
   Added all lakebase fields (`lakebase_table_exists`, `lakebase_database`,
   `lakebase_schema`, `lakebase_table`, `lakebase_synced_uc`, `lakebase_sync_mode`)
   to `dtwin_detail` so the Cockpit page has the same data as the Build page.
   Also switched `triple_count` to prefer `dt_existence` over `ts_status`.
3. src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js
   `_loadDtExistence()` now calls `_applyBuildGraphEngineUi(data)` before
   `_applyDtExistence(data)` so the Table existence badge is updated on the
   post-build refresh call.

Modified files:
- src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py
- src/back/objects/domain/HomeService.py
- src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js

Tests: pre-existing failures only (189 failed are from ongoing lakebase migration
unrelated to these changes); 1468 passed, 0 new failures introduced.

